======================================================================
DISC-8 ITEM 4b: THE CV = 1 LEAD
======================================================================

STEP 1: CV = 1 EQUIVALENCE (exact Fraction)

  x_i = 1 + a*cos(phi_i), phi_i at 120-degree spacing

  mean(x) = 1  [from sum cos = 0]

  var(x) = a^2/2 = 2/2 = 1
  mean(x) = 1
  CV^2 = var/mean^2 = 1/1 = 1
  CV = 1 iff a^2 = 2: True (EXACT)

  CHAIN OF EQUIVALENCES (all exact):
    Koide = 2/3
    <=> (1 + a^2/2)/3 = 2/3
    <=> a^2/2 = 1
    <=> var(x) = 1
    <=> var(x) = mean(x)^2
    <=> CV(x) = 1
    <=> sigma = mu for the sqrt(m) distribution

  All 4 equivalences verified as exact Fraction identities.

